comments.body:
@rhatdan @mheon I think it'd be best if instead of:
```
    pods, lastError := getPodsFromContext(c, runtime)                                                                                                                        
    if len(pods) == 0 && lastError != nil {                                                                                                                                  
        return lastError                                                                                                                                                     
    }
```
it was 
```
    // getPodsFromContext returns an error when a requested pod                                                                                                              
    // isn't found. The only fatal error scenerio is when there are no pods                                                                                                  
    // in which case the following loop will be skipped.                                                                                                                     
    pods, lastError := getPodsFromContext(c, runtime)                                                                                                                        
```
which looks cleaner, explains why nothing errored out, and is more efficient. 
If either of you want to keep it as is, no problem. Just thought I'd put in my final two cents before shipping
